{{! template-lint-disable block-indentation }}
<h2 id="title">Ember CLI Summer Note Editor</h2>
<div class="container-fluid">
  <div>
    <h3>Example </h3>
    {{summernote-editor
    disabled=disabled
    content=(readonly value)
    placeholder="Enter Content Here"
    onContentChange=(action (mut value))
    }}
    <p>Disable editing {{input type="checkbox" checked=disabled}}</p>
  </div>
  <div class="wysiwyg-preview">
    <div class="highlight">
      {{! template-lint-disable no-triple-curlies }}
      <pre>{{{value}}}</pre>
      {{! template-lint-enable no-triple-curlies }}
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="highlight">
    <pre>
  Use the following code to put a wysiwyg editor.

  &#123;&#123;summernote-editor
    focus=false
    btnSize=bs-sm
    airMode=false
    header=header
    height=height
    buttons=buttons
    toolbar=toolbar
    disabled=disabled
    callbacks=callbacks
    content=(readonly value)
    placeholder="Enter Content Here"
    onContentChange=(action (mut value))
  &#125;&#125;
    </pre>
  </div>
  All callbacks except <b>onChange</b> are supported. The <b>onChange</b> callback are used internally for the <b>onContentChange</b> action.
  <div class="highlight">
    <pre>
  callbackOptions: {
    onInit: function() {
    console.log('Summernote is launched');
    },
    onEnter: function() {
    console.log('Enter/Return key pressed');
    },
    onPaste: function(e) {
    console.log('Called event paste');
    },
  },
  </pre>
  </div>
</div>
{{! template-lint-enable block-indentation }}
